Traffic / Signalization project Engineer
- ,
Date Posted: 2014/05/05 19:38:26
Ref. JB3047567
Job Description
We are searching for a Signalization and Traffic Project Engineer for an important European Company
We are looking for a Project Engineer with experience in Traffic Management and IT System for projects in Makkah and Medina.
The candidate selected will have to manage moderate size projects with high complexity. This includes initiating, planning, executing, controlling and closing of customer projects.
Will be necessary an experience on similar position of 3 - 5 years
Languages: High level of English and Arabic is required.
Candidates will be based on site activity in Makah and Medina
Skills
Project Engineer with experience in Traffic Management and IT System for projects in Makkah and Medina
 Project Management, Traffic Engineering, Transport Planning and Master Planning.
 Parking Management, Parking Studies, Parking Master Planning and Parking Solutions.
 Traffic Analysis, Traffic Impact Studies, Traffic Safety Studies, Traffic Calming and Operational Analysis.
 Manual Formulation, Site Surveys, De-Bottlenecking and Flow Management.
 System Tracking, Development and Up gradation.
 Manual and Automatic Traffic Counts, Turning Movement Counts, Roadside Interviews, Household Surveys.
 Parking Turn Over Surveys, Land Use Surveys and Journey Time Surveys.
 SATURN, VISSIM, Synchro, aaSIDRA, HCS2000, AIMSUN and VISSUM, AutoCAD and MapInfo.
Will be necessary an experience on similar position of 3 - 5 years
